snippet: Jamal Yousef, a former member of the Syrian military pleaded guilty on Friday in federal court in Manhattan to conspiracy to provide material support to a Colombian terrorist organization.
abstract: Jamal Yousef, former member of the Syrian military, pleads guilty to conspiracy to provide military-grade weapons to terrorist group Revolutionary Armed Forces of Columbia for hundreds of kilograms of cocaine.
lead_paragraph: Jamal Yousef, a former member of the Syrian military pleaded guilty on Friday in federal court in Manhattan to conspiracy to provide material support to a Colombian terrorist organization.

headline.seo: Jamal Yousef Pleads Guilty in FARC Conspiracy Case
headline.main: Guilty Plea in Conspiracy Case Linked to Colombian Guerrillas
